	<!-- Introduction -->
	<!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
	<purpose>
	<p> 
      This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the 
      representation of members certain commonly-used datatypes. 
      Representation of the following kinds of values are covered in this 
 	  part of ISO 10303: 
    </p> 
          <ul> 
              <li>boolean value (value that are either true or false);</li> 
              <li>integer value (value that is a whole number);</li> 
              <li>rational value (value that can be represented as an integer divided by another integer, the second integer 
 				being nonnegative);</li> 
              <li>real value;</li> 
              <li>value that is a sequence (an ordered collection) of other values;</li> 
              <li>value that is a set (an unordered collection with no duplicates) of other values.</li> 
          </ul> 
                 <note>
                 Representation of a value that is a string is covered in module 
                 <module_ref linkend="foundation_representation:introduction">Foundation representation</module_ref>.
 				</note>
   	
	</purpose>
	<!-- Items in scope -->
	<inscope>
